HEADWORD: Thatching
<hw>Thatch"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act or art of
covering buildings with thatch; so as to keep out rain, snow,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The materials used for this purpose;
thatch.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thaught</ent>⟦br⟧
